Jax does do the crazy damages quite well.

After a long thought and doing some scholarly tea sipping, I believe one has to specify what role the champion is fulfilling in order to judge how well they are designed. It's difficult to compare a Mage to an AD Carry or a Tank to a Support because they're roles, mechanics, playstyle, theme, and kits are all different. Here's what I think in terms of roles:  

**Best Designed Tank:** {{champion:54}}   
I believe Malphite is the best  designed tank because of his high armor scaling, great interrupt, CC, AoE and single target mixed damage, and overall tankiness. For a giant, sentient rock, Malphite fits the bill perfectly.

**Best Designed Jungler:** {{champion:72}}   
I believe Skarner is the best designed jungler because of his low cooldowns along with self reducing timers, quick clear time, strong, spammable, low cost AoE damage, high survivability with a shield, high mobility, great dueler and brawler, line-style slow, and the greatest form of CC with his suppression, Skarner makes a great bruiser in the jungle. He is a scorpion made of crystals!

**Best Designed Mage:** {{champion:34}}  
I believe Anivia is the best designed mage/caster because of her weak resistances, rebirthing opportunity, spammable CC, high burst damage, great interrupt and confusion inducing wall, AoE circle of wintry death, and good poke. Anivia players value timing and precision, making her a great mage. Her theme is also executed very well.

**Best Designed Support:** {{champion:37}}  
Although she may be weak as of right now, Sona is by far one of the best designed supports. She has great healing and sustain, spammable poke, mobility, and engage. She brings a lot of utility which is what a support should do.

**Best Designed ADC:** {{champion:133}}  
Quinn (and Valor) is the best designed ADC because of her strong poke and attack damage, AoE blind, scouting power, great reposition, and an amazing ultimate bundled with gap closers, blinds, and an AoE execute. Quinn, the falconer, makes great use of the theme.

Of course, these are my opinions and most people will not agree with me. But hey, thats all part of the discussion!

