Those are just my favourites in terms of each lane/starting place. 

Role-wise, I have to say I love Voli and Malphite as tanks, and as much as I hate him in game, Talon is the best assassin ever. I don't play her, but Sona is a pretty solid support when played well, and Ziggs is the best AP carry by far.

Some people might argue with me and that's fine, but I really think Ziggs is the best champion Rito has put out. He doesn't have an innate burstiness (cough LB), so he takes some skill in fights, which IMO is more fun. Bouncing Bomb skill-shots and timing/placement of ults and satchels are key. People say he's useless without blue buff, but I just get Tear of the Goddess early, and farm up my mana with that. If I'm lacking mana mid to late game, I get Iceborn Gauntlet. 

Beyond play-style, Ziggs has the best character/personality IMO. The crazy explosives-obsessed yordle aspect is awesome, and his care-free, oblivious nature is hilarious. 


{{champion:115}} "Whaddya mean, it doesn't look safe?"

Maybe I'm biased, as I was quite a chemistry nerd in high school and still love explosions (the legal type, of course), but I just love everything about Ziggs. Rito, please never change him. :D

Jax is far from best designed.  As it stands right now, he's very overpowered.  He's like Lee Sin, except instead of bouncing back and forth, he dives in and pentakills the team with no risk.  I feel with number tweaks to make Tank Jax less effective, like they did with Vi, Jax will be balanced. As for who I think the best designed champions are, here is my opinion

**Best Tank**

{{champion:12}} 

The cow has seen better days, but he's THE tank.  He definitely embodies the idea of getting in your opponent's face and tossing them around.  Braum is an honorable mention here.

**Best ADC**

{{champion:51}} 

People cry about Caitlyn being overpowered, but she is the "Renekton bar" for marksmen.  She has solid damage, abilities, and escape options.  Vayne is an honorable mention here.

**Best Support**

{{champion:412}} 

Do I really need to elaborate on this?  Thresh is just an amazing support.  He has a great kit for helping your team out.  Braum is an honorable mention here.

**Best Mage**

{{champion:115}} 

Ziggs is great for very similar reasons as Caitlyn.  Great escape options, and solid damage.  Ahri is an honorable mention here.

**Best Assassin**

{{champion:157}} 

I consider Yasuo more of an assassin than a fighter.  He has some great juking potential, and he has great sustain, poke, gap clear, and crowd control.  Zed is an honorable mention here.

**Best Jungler**

{{champion:77}} 

He may not be meta anymore, but Udyr has some of the best jungle clear and sustain out of any champion.  He can easily burst down champions, and despite his vulnerability to crowd control, he's easily one of the best carries in the game.  Vi is an honorable mention here.

**Best Bruiser**

{{champion:126}} 

Jayce just has a fantastic kit.  I'd say despite the clear cooldown and mana constraints on him, Jayce definitely embodies how a 6 ability champion with no ultimate can still be a ton of fun.  Lee Sin is an honorable mention here.

****

*Worst Champions*

**Worst Tank**

{{champion:6}} 

Urgot is just... I don't even know what Urgot is.  He's ranged, but he has lower attack range than Thresh.  He's a tank, so why is he ranged?  His ultimate just doesn't make sense for his kit, and honestly nothing else really does either.

**Worst ADC**

{{champion:22}} 

Cue the downvotes.  Ashe just doesn't have anything that really makes her a worthwhile ADC.  Her passive is atrocious, she doesn't have an escape, and she doesn't really have poke either, despite having formerly the longest range in the game.


**Worst Support**

{{champion:53}} 

This guy is not a support.  He's a bruiser who's been overnerfed.  His kit is very toxic in terms of the kind of gameplay in bot lane.  Post 6 he'll start to take CS, and he just doesn't belong in bot lane in this meta.

**Worst Mage**

{{champion:34}} 

Anivia is extremely squishy and doesn't have the damage to back it up.  She just all around isn't very fun or satisfying to play.

**Worst Assassin**

{{champion:28}} 

Her kit is just putrid.  The only think assassin like about her is her passive, and it's the easiest stealth to reveal.

**Worst Jungler**

{{champion:33}} 

Rammus has some very strong ganks, but when it comes to sustain, he's just way too lacking.  His Q is his bread and butter however, and there really isn't a use to it outside of the jungle.

**Worst Bruiser**

{{champion:41}} 

Gangplank has a serious identity crisis.  He's supposed to be a duelist, but has no attack speed steroid.  He's supposed to be a carry, but is massively outscaled by pretty much every duelist in the game.  He's supposed to be great in teamfights, but his ultimate is just not good enough.  GP is my favorite champion, but he's not fit for purpose.  Jack of All Trades, Master of None.

**Worst Champion**

{{champion:83}} 

Alas poor Yorick.  Yorick is the embodiment of how NOT to create a champion.  He has no counters, yet he is completely useless past laning phase.  He's not fun to play, nor play against.
